How does yoga make YOU feel. There was a time in my life when yoga helped me stop feeling...like a bandaid. And that's how many people like us find yoga, to ease pain. Then, one day you realize that the only way to invite change is to use your yoga as a gateway to understanding the pain and working through it, rather than numbing it. #yoga #yogajourney üì∏ @actionhiro Wearing @aloyoga

See that cute little beach dog? Managing the photo shoot was a bit stressful that day but as soon as this little doggie got in the shot, it made all of us smile! I have 3 dogs and every time I pay attention to them, they bring my mind into the present moment. Giving them a hug or sitting with one of them is incredibly soothing and, if your dog is calm enough, he/she can be the best meditation pal. Our yoga teacher trainings are working toward being completely family friendly...wouldn't it be cool if they were pet friendly too?!! üòÇüòÇ üê∂ üì∏ @jake_paul_white

Community is more important than we realize. When I first started teaching yoga almost a decade ago, I did everything by myself. It was tough, lonely and I wasn't making any money to support my daughter or myself. But, when I started to reach out to the community around me, my teaching career started to flourish. It's so easy to get lost in competition and feel threatened by the incredibly talented teachers out there. But, there is truly room for everyone and the best projects are the ones I've collaborated with people on. Like the upcoming 200hr Yoga Teacher Training we are co-teaching with @mackenzieyoga and @mathieuboldronyoga !! There is still some room so join us this June 18-July 14 for a life changing and immersive Yoga experience. More info via the link in our bio. #yogateachertraining #fitflowflytraining #fitflowfly

We showed up, got real, cracked open, harnessed our power, trusted, supported, cared, cried, hugged and held each other. It was fun and hard, educational but confronting. This past 300hr Yoga Teacher training was truly a life-changing experience. Although I'm still processing the effects of it, I know I have grown, my mind is clear, my heart open. Wishing all of you amazing teachers the same. ‚ù§üôèüòòüí™ This past month has truly been a life changing experience and each and everyone of you has impacted my life and helped me grow. See you all soon.
